{"title":"In Stock for Now: The Radavist x REALM Camera Bag and The Radavist x Roly-Poly Instant Coffee!","link":"https://theradavist.com/radavist-realm-camera-bag-roly-poly-instant-coffee/","date":1741086045000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Radavist_Realm_Roly_Poly_Four_UP.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Radavist_Realm_Roly_Poly_Four_UP.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Radavist_Realm_Roly_Poly_Four_UP.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Radavist_Realm_Roly_Poly_Four_UP.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>Today, we’re elated to finally release two collaborations with companies we love and value here at The Radavist. We wanted to pour our hearts into two things we feel passionate about: photography and coffee. So we teamed up with <a href=\"https://shop-realm.com/\" target=\"_blank\">REALM</a> to design our first-ever camera bag and pinged Bozeman, Montana’s <a href=\"https://rolypoly.coffee/\" target=\"_blank\">Roly-Poly Coffee</a>, to help formulate our first-ever instant coffee. Let’s take a closer look below.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-1.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-1.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://shop.theradavist.com/products/instant-coffee-the-radavist-x-roly-poly-deserted-blend\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist x Roly-Poly Coffee Instant Deserted Blend</a> ($17)</h3>\n<p>After last year’s release of <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/in-stock-for-now-roly-poly-coffee-radavist-deserted-blend/\" target=\"_blank\">our Roly-Poly Coffee collaboration</a>, Taylor asked if we wanted to do anything for 2025 to which we immediately replied: “Instant!” Taking our unique Deserted blend of Kenya and Ethiopia coffee, we shipped beans to Swift Coffee, the industry’s leading crystallization experts to make instant crystals from it.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-3.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-3.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-4.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The result is a very unique and flavorful offering in the instant coffee scene with rich honey and fruity notes.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-6.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-6.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-6.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-7.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-7.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-7.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/RadavistRolyPolyInstant-7.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>So, when you’re on your next ultralight trip, you can enjoy this premium African blend of Kenyan and Ethiopian beans instead of suffering through some cowboy coffee swill—unless you like to roll with grounds in your teeth. No judgment.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>6 premium instant coffee packets per box</li>\n<li>$17 (that’s $2.83 per cup for the accounting peeps)</li>\n<li>Just add 10oz of hot or cold liquid and stir</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Pick up a box in <a href=\"https://shop.theradavist.com/products/instant-coffee-the-radavist-x-roly-poly-deserted-blend\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist webshop</a> and at Roly-Poly’s Bozeman locations today!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-14.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-14.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-14.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://shop.theradavist.com/products/camera-hip-bag-the-radavist-x-realm\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist x REALM Camera Bag</a> ($135)</h3>\n<p>Carrying a camera while riding bikes is a big part of what we do over here at The Radavist. As you might imagine, we’ve got a lot of ideas surrounding the best way to carry a camera on the bike and through almost 19 years experience in doing so, we put all those ideas into a bag with our friends at Realm.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-3.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-3.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-3.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-4.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-4.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-4.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This represents the most secure and minimal camera toting setup we’ve used. Taking Realm’s Cross-body bag, we added padding, pockets, a sternum strap, with plenty of space for a mirrorless or DSLR camera. In fact, this bag fits a Canon R5 and 70-200 lens!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-33.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-33.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-33.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-33.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-39.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-39.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-39.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-39.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-27.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-27.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>John has been using various prototypes of this bag for a few years now. He and Hanson from Realm worked on dialing in the silhouette to make it a perfect cross-body or hip bag, depending on your riding style.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-22.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-22.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-17.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-17.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>It’s not just for on-the-bike riding, either. Use this bag as a day pack for errands or sightseeing while traveling or just to carry your camera around for a day. It’s secure, stable, and is small enough to fit under a rain jacket if it rains. The biggest difference between this bag and others we’ve used is that it is wider, doesn’t protrude a lot from the back, and you can really cinch down on it to make it stable while riding.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-41.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-41.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-41.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-41.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-40.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-40.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-40.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-40.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-35.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-35.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-35.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Our first run of these bags features a natural, undyed X-Pac outer with hi-vis safety orange on the inside to make it easy to find your goods. We added our Radavist Jackal to the underside and hi-vis orange zipper pulls.</p>\n<p><em>Knowing how important it is to keep your camera and your body safe in the event of a crash, there is extra padding on the back of the bag and additional padding on the inside.</em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-28.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-28.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-11.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-11.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/The-Radavist-Realm-Camera-Bag-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>We wanted this bag to look great as new but to carry a nice patina from muddy rides. If you prefer to keep it natural-colored, some OxyClean or vinegar and baking soda will restore it to its original palette.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/DSC_5325.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/DSC_5325.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/DSC_5325.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/DSC_5325.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>X-Pac water-resistant exterior fabric</li>\n<li>400d water resistant packcloth hi-vis safety orange liner fabric</li>\n<li>Daisy chain across front exterior</li>\n<li>Zippered outer pocket, zippered inner pocket, and 2-slot inner slip pocket</li>\n<li>Water resistant zippers with silent 550 safety orange paracord zipper pulls (made in US)</li>\n<li>Padded inner divider, placement is adjustable with velcro attachment</li>\n<li>1.5″ wide main strap, adjustable up to 56″ with lightweight Fidlock magnetic buckle</li>\n<li>Removable sternum stabilizer strap</li>\n<li>Air mesh back panel, with additional closed cell foam padding (made in US) for structure and comfort</li>\n<li>Cinch straps on bottom</li>\n<li>Embroidered jackal on bottom,</li>\n<li>12″ wide, 7″ tall, 4.5″deep</li>\n<li>Made in the US of A by <a href=\"https://shop-realm.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Realm</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Pick one up in <a href=\"https://shop.theradavist.com/products/camera-hip-bag-the-radavist-x-realm\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist webshop</a> today!</p>\n<p><em>As always, every cent from your webshop purchases goes to keeping the lights on over here and we greatly appreciate the support. Thank you!</em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/radavist-realm-camera-bag-roly-poly-instant-coffee/\">In Stock for Now: The Radavist x REALM Camera Bag and The Radavist x Roly-Poly Instant Coffee!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"ffd44e8751b6c79f908f6e197f49671c70f379e65ffd85ea487b9d189b248dd0","category":"Cycling"}